TITLE: Top psychologist: IQ is the No. 1 predictor of work success—especially combined with these 5 traits
SUMMARY: Does a high IQ definitely set you up for more success down the road – be it in terms of career advancement or higher salaries? The answer, essentially, is yes, according to researchers.

TITLE: Europe on high alert as Russia temporarily halts gas flows via major pipeline
SUMMARY: Europe fears the suspension of deliveries could be extended beyond the 10-day timeline, derailing the region's winter supply preparations.

TITLE: Twitter shares sink after Elon Musk terminates $44 billion deal
SUMMARY: Twitter shares sank sharply after Elon Musk said he is trying to terminate his $44 billion takeover of the company.

TITLE: Klarna valuation plunges 85% to $6.7 billion as 'buy now, pay later' hype fades
SUMMARY: Klarna said it raised $800 million in fresh funding at a $6.7 billion valuation — down sharply from $45.6 billion a year ago.

TITLE: India set to overtake China as the world's most populous country in 2023, UN says
SUMMARY: The United Nations' report was released on World Population Day.

SUMMARY: It could be in the interests of both employers and employees to return to the office full time, future of work author Steve Cadigan says.

SUMMARY: The odds of the U.S. economy falling into recession by next year are greater than 50%, TD Securities said Monday, outlining three possible ways it could get hit.

TITLE: Stocks slide to start the week as Wall Street prepares for earnings season to kick off
SUMMARY: Wall Street is looking ahead to big company earnings reports and key inflation data, on the heels of a strong employment report.

SUMMARY: Djokovic has consistently refused Covid vaccination — a stance that cost him the opportunity to compete at the Australian Open earlier this year, Sky Sports reports.

SUMMARY: June consumer inflation data and the start of the second-quarter earnings season could be two catalysts that make for bumpy markets in the week ahead.

SUMMARY: Invesco said the political uncertainty means the U.K. economy will continue to "wither" in the interim.

SUMMARY: Megan Keaveny made $3,000 by giving up her seat on a Delta flight. Experts say airlines will likely continue paying passengers lucratively throughout the summer.

SUMMARY: Hong Kong's Hang Seng index fell around 3% after news that China has imposed fines on heavyweights Tencent and Alibaba.

SUMMARY: Softening demand is the latest threat to world trade, after two years of supply chain disruptions.

SUMMARY: "Twitter has not complied with its contractual obligations," an attorney for Musk wrote.

SUMMARY: "Thor: Love and Thunder" tallied $143 million during its domestic debut, pushing the overall weekend haul to more than $200 million.

TITLE: Amazon Prime Day is coming up: Here's why deal experts say you might want to skip it this year
SUMMARY: Just because something is discounted on Prime Day doesn't mean it's the best deal you'll see anywhere, or even all year.

SUMMARY: Charles Schwab's annual Modern Wealth Survey found that in some U.S. cities, it takes a net worth over $1 million to be seen as "financially comfortable."
